      • getURLBase

        public java.lang.String getURLBase(java.net.URL fileURL)
        Description copied from interface: AboutManager
        Returns the base path of a file URL.

        The method will simply cut the last path of the URL. For example, if the URL is:

        http://www.gvsig.org/docs/file.html

        The returned base string would be:

        http://www.gvsig.org/docs/
        Specified by:
        getURLBase in interface AboutManager
        Parameters:
        fileURL - the URL of the file
        Returns:
        the base path of a file URL
